			"entries": [
				"You momentarily open two interconnected portals, one directly beneath a creature you can see within range, and the other just above it. If the creature is not flying, it must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or fall through these portals in a loop for 30 feet, before the portals vanish and the creature lands back in its original space and takes falling damage."
			],
