			"entries": [
				"One creature of your choice that you can see within range must each make a Intelligence saving throw. For the duration, creatures that fail this saving throw can only breathe by maintaining {@status Concentration|XPHB} on breathing (as if {@status Concentration|XPHB|Concentrating} on a spell).",
				"A creature under the effect of this spell that is not {@status Concentration|XPHB|Concentrating} on breathing is not able to hold their breath, immediately starting to suffocate. Creatures that are suffocating gain 1 level of {@condition Exhaustion|XPHB} at the end of each of their turns. When a creature can breathe again, it removes all levels of {@condition Exhaustion|XPHB} it gained from suffocating.",
				"Creatures that are suffocating as a result of this spell may expend an Action to start {@status Concentration|XPHB|Concentrating} on breathing."
			],
