			"entries": [
				"When you or a creature within 5 feet of you is the target of an attack, you can use your reaction to erect a crude, yet sturdy wall of earth in an attempt to block it.",
				"When you cast this spell, you conjure a wall of earth 10 feet wide, 10 feet tall, and up to 5 feet thick that immediately juts up between you and your attacker. This wall remains for 1 minute before crumbling back into the ground. The wall provides 3/4 {@variantrule cover|XPHB} for up to two medium or smaller creatures, including against the triggering attack. If the wall is created in the same space as a creature, that creature is pushed 5 feet back away from the origin point of the wall.",
				"The wall is an object made of earth that can be damaged and thus breached. Each 5 cubic feet has AC 10 and 10 Hit Points per foot of thickness, and it has Immunity to Poison and Psychic damage. Reducing a portion to 0 Hit Points destroys it and might cause connected portions to collapse at the DM’s discretion."
			],
