			"entries": [
				"When you cast this spell, describe one specific task that you wish to accomplish. You create an improvised tool capable of aiding in the completion of that task, which appears within an unoccupied space within range. The tool is Tiny or Small, taking on an appearance you describe. For the duration, a creature has advantage on all ability checks made to accomplish the specified task, provided it is holding the tool. The tool disassembles into its components when the spell ends. ",
				"The task you describe must be specific in nature, as adjudicated by the DM. For example, you could create a tool which helps you to navigate a dense forest, to craft a specific item or to locate a specific kind of object, but you couldn’t create a tool which helps you to ‘defeat all evil’, or ‘accomplish all my goals’."
			],
