			"entries": [
				"When you cast this spell, you conjure a magical gatling gun which manifests in your hands. As an Action while you are {@status Concentration|XPHB|Concentrating} on this spell, you can pull the trigger, firing 2 magical bullets. Each bullet races towards a target within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target with {@variantrule Advantage|XPHB} for each bullet. On a hit, the bullet deals {@damage 1d4} Force damage. You can direct the bullets to aim at one creature or several.",
				{
					"type": "list",
					"style": "list-hang-notitle",
					"items": [
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Wind Up",
							"entries": [
								"For each consecutive turn you use an {@variantrule Action|XPHB} to pull the trigger of the magic machine gun, you fire 2 additional magical bullets, up to a maximum of 6 bullets per turn as a 3rd-level spell. For each turn the trigger isn't pulled, the amount of bullets fired per turn is reduced by 1."
							]
						}
					]
				}
			],
			"source": "CoopersCompendiumofComplexities",
			"components": {
				"v": true,
				"s": true
			},
			"entriesHigherLevel": [
				{
					"type": "entries",
