			"entries": [
				"You speak a word of power that causes a flurry of deep lacerations to cover  the body of one creature you can see within range, as if slashed by several {@condition invisible} swords. The target immediately takes {@damage 3d8} Slashing damage.",
				"Additionally, the target must make a Constitution Saving Throw. On a failure, the target begins hemorrhaging blood. While {@condition bleeding|MonstersOfDrakkenheim}, the target loses {@dice 1d8} {@variantrule Hit Points|XPHB} at the start of each of its turns. The wounds close after 1 minute, after a spell or potion resotres {@variantrule Hit Points|XPHB} to the target, or after the target or a creature within 5 feet of it takes an {@variantrule Action|XPHB} to stanch the wound, doing so by succeeding on a DC 12 Wisdom ({@skill Medicine|XPHB}) check. On a success, the creature does not begin {@condition bleeding|MonstersOfDrakkenheim}. Creatures that do not have blood or some similar bodily fluid, and creatures that are immune to Slashing damage automatically suceed on the Constitution Saving Throw."
			],
			"source": "CoopersCompendiumofComplexities",
