			"entries": [
				"You create a flaming tornado in a cylinder 20 feet wide and 50 feet tall centered on a point within range. Until the spell ends, it emits bright light in a 40 foot Radius and dim light in an additional 20 feet.",
				"When the vortex appears, each creature in it makes a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes {@damage 5d8} Fire damage and begins {@hazard burning|XPHB}. On a successful save, a creature takes half a much damage only. A creature also makes this save when the spell's area moves into its space and when it enters the spell's area or ends its turn there. A creature makes the save only once per turn.",
				"On your turn after casting the spell, you can take a {@action Magic|XPHB} action to move the spell area up to 30 feet."
