			"entries": [
				"You call forth the glorious spirit of a giant. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range and uses the {@creature Giant Spirit|CoopersCompendiumofComplexities} stat block. When you cast the spell, choose a type: Cloud, Fire, Frost, Hill, Stone, or Storm. The creature resembles a giant of its type, which determines certain details in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 Hit Points or when the spell ends.",
				"The creature is an ally to you and your allies. In combat, the creature shares your Initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no {@variantrule action|XPHB} required by you). If you don't issue any, it takes the {@action Dodge|XPHB} action and uses its movement to avoid danger."
