			"entries": [
				"You conjure a fiery phoenix that blazes across the battlefield. A phoenix made of flame appears in an unoccupied space of your choice within range and immediately moves up to 60 feet in a straight line, stopping early if it encounters an impassable barrier. The phoenix can pass through openings large enough for a Tiny creature.",
				"At the end of its movement, the phoenix erupts in an explosion of magical fire. All creatures in its path, as well as those within a 15-foot Radius of the point where it explodes must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes {@damage 7d8} Fire damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful one.",
				"After the explosion, the phoenix leaves behind a hovering ember at the point where it detonated. The ember remains for the duration of the spell.",
				"When in full form, the phoenix emits bright light in a 20 foot Radius and dim light in an additional 10 feet. The ember left behind emits dim light in a 5 foot Radius.",
				{
					"type": "list",
					"style": "list-hang-notitle",
					"items": [
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Reviving the Phoenix",
							"entries": [
								"As an action on your turn, you can command the ember to reconstitute into the phoenix. When you do, the phoenix reforms in the ember's space, moves up to 60 feet in a straight line, and explodes again. The ember then returns to its new detonation point. This effect can be repeated until the spell ends."
							]
						}
					]
				}
