			"entries": [
				"You speak a word with such heat that it causes one creature you can see within range to spontaneously combust. If the target has 150 {@variantrule Hit Points|XPHB} or fewer, it immediately takes {@damage 8d6} Fire damage and is set alight with extra-hot blue fire. Otherwise, the spell has no effect.",
				"While {@hazard burning|XPHB} as a result of this spell, the target sheds bright light in a 30-foot Radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet, and it takes {@damage 2d6} Fire damage at the start of each of its turns. All damage dealt by this spell ignores resistance to Fire damage. The target can make a Dexterity check against your spell save DC at the end of each of its turns. On a success, this {@hazard burning|XPHB} effect ends.",
				"The magical flames created by this spell cannot be extinguished by nonmagical means. If damage from this spell kills a target, the target is turned to ash."
