						"source": "XPHB"
					}
				]
			},
			"entries": [
				"Making a Binding Vow requires three people; the two who are making the vow, and a third party acting as the witness. Any of the three may be the caster of the spell. All three creatures must be willing, and the two creatures to be bound must clasp their arms. The spell fails if any of the creatures is {@condition Charmed|XPHB} or has an Intelligence of 4 or less.",
				"As part of casting the spell, the caster dictates up to three Vows, each spoken aloud in a language all three creatures can speak and no longer than 25 words each, and in the form of a question. The 25-word limit does not include words that make the sentence a question or the name of the person being addressed (e.g. \"Will you, Johnathan Doe...?\").",
				"Each Vow must apply to one or both creatures and, after each is spoken, both creatures must clearly affirm their consent. If either creature refuses at any point, the spell fails. The caster must then state aloud that the consequence for violating any of the Vows is immediate, unavoidable death. This consequence must be acknowledged and consented to by both creatures that are to be bound. A creature that dies as a result of violating a Binding Vow cannot be resurrected or revived in any way short of direct action from the gods.",
				"If the spell is successfully cast, it takes hold until the contents of all Vows are met, any Vow is violated, or if both the targets of the spell willingly clasp their arms again to end the spell. {@spell Dispel Magic} cannot end the effects of the spell, and {@spell Wish} has a 50% chance of failing when cast with the purpose of ending the spell. Each participant is instantly aware when the spell ends and how it ended."
			],
			"source": "CoopersCompendiumofComplexities",
			"components": {
				"v": true,
				"s": true,
				"m": {
					"text": "a silver braid worth at least 500 gold and up to three gems of the same kind each worth at least 333 gold each, each gem representing one Vow, all of which the spell consumes",
					"consume": true,
					"cost": 83300
				}
			},
			"miscTags": [
				"PRM"
			]
		},
