			"entries": [
				"You rain massive shards of ice and a blinding blanket of snow from the sky over a wide area surrounding a point within range. The resulting impact creates a {@condition frozen|MonstersOfDrakkenheim} fog over the area. Each creature in a 60-foot Radius sphere centered on the chosen point must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes {@damage 6d8} Cold damage and {@damage 6d6} Slashing damage. On a successful save, it takes half as much damage.",
				"The same 60-foot sphere is filled with a chilling fog that lasts for 1 minute. The entire area within the spell's sphere is Heavily Obscured. It lasts for the duration or until a strong wind (such as one created by {@spell Gust of Wind}) disperses it. Any creature that starts its turn within the fog must make a Constitution saving throw. A creatures {@damage 2d6} Cold damage on a failure, or half as much on a success. "
