			"entries": [
				"You conjure a blazing miniature sun above your open hand that radiates unbearable heat and sunlight in a 60-foot emanation until the end of your next turn. The sunlight's area is bright light, dispels magical darkness, and sheds dim light for an additional 60 feet.",
				{
					"type": "list",
					"style": "list-hang-notitle",
					"items": [
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Solar Burst",
							"entries": [
								"When the sun appears, each creature in the area must make a Constitution saving throw, taking {@damage 6d8} Fire damage and {@damage 6d8} Radiant damage on a failed save, or half a much on a successful one. In addition, nonmagical objects within the spell's area start {@condition burning|MonstersOfDrakkenheim} if flammable and any viable metal items are affected as if by {@spell Heat Metal} for the duration."
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Solar Lance",
							"entries": [
								"While the sun hovers above your hand, you can take a bonus action to launch it in a 10-foot wide, 120-foot long line. Each creature in the line makes a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes {@damage 6d6} Fire damage and {@damage 6d6} Radiant damage and is pushed by the sun 20 feet towards the end of the line. On a successful save, it takes half as much damage only."
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Pride Flare",
							"entries": [
								"Until the spell ends, you can take a bonus action to cause the sun to erupt in a blaze, ending the spell. Each creature in a 120-foot emanation around the sun must make a Constitution saving throw, taking {@damage 12d8} Fire damage and {@damage 12d8} Radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much on a successful one."
							]
						}
					]
				}
			],
