						"source": "XPHB"
					}
				]
			},
			"entries": [
				"You weave the threads of knowledge through the intricate and fragile noospheric space of the world, plucking a single piece of information from the collective consciousness of all sentient beings and existing records. When you cast this spell, you must choose a single piece of information from the following list:",
				{
					"type": "list",
					"style": "list",
					"items": [
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "",
							"entries": [
								"The full, exact name of a single creature or item (e.g., 'Antonius Succo,' or 'The Sword of Vengeance')."
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "",
							"entries": [
								"The full, exact name of a collection or type of item, limited to no more than 100 individual items (e.g., 'The Keys of the Dragons')."
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "",
							"entries": [
								"The full, exact name of a single specific location, limited to an area no larger than a 5-mile cube (e.g. 'Trisula')."
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "",
							"entries": [
								"The exact location of a single place, limited to an area no larger than a 5-mile cube (e.g. 'where I was born')."
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "",
							"entries": [
								"The effect(s) of a specific item or how to use it."
							]
						}
					]
				},
				"You may choose another piece of information other than one described here, and your DM will determine whether your choice is suitable or how it would be affected if you do so.",
				"Once the spell is complete, the chosen information is immediately expunged. All creatures, except for you, immediately forget it, leaving an absence in their memories where the information should be. To them, the missing information does not and has never existed, and therefore they are unable to recollect it. Furthermore, all existing records (books, signs, scrolls, audio, video, etc.) containing the information are instantly and irrevocably corrupted, leaving only blank spaces, static, or nonsensical gibberish in its place.",
				"However, if the caster shares the expunged information in any way whether verbally, through writing, or through any other medium, the effect of this spell immediately ends. The piece of information is instantaneously restored to the collective consciousness of all sentient beings and all existing records, returning to its original state.",
				"You can cast this spell only once. After casting it, the means to do so are permanently forgotten and thereafter incomrpehensible to you.",
				{
					"type": "item",
					"name": "Components",
					"entries": [
						"The material component for this spell is the sacrifice of one profound and intimate memory from your own life (such as a loved one's identity, the location of your childhood home, or your own true name). As a consequence, you no longer retain that memory and permanently lose the ability to perceive or process it. For you and you alone, anything relating to the memory is replaced by a permanent sensory and mental block."
					]
				},
				{
					"type": "list",
					"style": "list",
					"items": [
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Verbal",
							"entries": [
								"If information of the memory is audibly spoken to you (e.g., someone says the name of the loved one you sacrificed), the sound is replaced by an instantaneous burst of white noise or a sudden, deafening silence."
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Visual",
							"entries": [
								"If you glimpse or read any information relating to the memory in any language (e.g., in a book or on a map), the text or image is replaced by a blank space, gibberish, or a painful sensation in your eyes."
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Proximal",
							"entries": [
								"If you physically interact with the subject of the memory (e.g., standing in the location of your childhood home), you will immediately fall {@condition unconscious}. Every 1 minute you remain {@condition unconscious}, you will take {@damage 4d8} Psychic damage. This damage cannot be mitigated or resisted by any means. You will remain in this state for as long as you are interacting with the subject."
							]
						}
					]
				}
			],
			"source": "CoopersCompendiumofComplexities",
