			"entries": [
				"You tear a hole in space-time, causing motes of kaleidoscopic light to rain down. The tear forms at a Point you can see and spreads out to a radious of 150 feet. The tear sheds bright light within the Radius and for an additional 200 feet, and dim light for additional 350 feet after that.",
				"When summoned, and each round you maintain {@status Concentration|XPHB} on this spell, the tear releases a different color light at the start of your turn. Each color light requires creatures no more than 5,000 feet below the tear to make saving throws or suffer unique effects based on the color.",
				{
					"type": "list",
					"style": "list-hang-notitle",
					"items": [
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "When Summoned (Red)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes {@damage 8d6} Force damage, or half as much on a success.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 2 (Orange)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes {@damage 8d6} Fire damage, or half as much on a success.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 3 (Yellow)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes {@damage 8d6} Acid damage, or half as much on a success.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 4 (Green)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes {@damage 8d6} Lightning damage, or half as much on a success.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 5 (Blue)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes {@damage 8d6} Cold damage, or half as much on a success.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 6 (Pink)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain are {@condition Blinded|XPHB} and {@condition Charmed|XPHB}. A creature must then make a Wisdom saving throw at the start of your next turn. A successful Save ends the Blindness and the Charm. If it fails that saving throw, the creature is transported to another plane of existence of the DM's choosing and is no longer {@condition Blinded|XPHB}.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 7 (White)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes {@damage 8d6} Radiant damage, or half as much on a success.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 8 (Black)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes {@damage 8d6} Necrotic damage, or half as much on a success.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 9 (Purple)",
							"entries": [
								"Creatures in the rain are {@condition Restrained|XPHB}. A creature must then make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, it has the {@condition Restrained|XPHB} condition for 3 rounds. On a successful save, its Speed is 0 until the start of your next turn.<br><br>A {@condition Restrained|XPHB} target makes another Constitution saving throw at the end of each of its turns. If it successfully saves against this spell three times, it no longer needs to make Constitution saving throws to avoid effects from this spell for the remainder of the duration. If it fails its saves three times, it is {@condition Petrified|XPHB} until the condition is ended by {@spell Greater Restoration} or similar magic. The successes and failures needn't be consecutive; keep track of both until the target collects three of a kind.<br><br>"
							]
						},
						{
							"type": "item",
							"name": "Round 10 (Chaos)",
							"entries": [
								"The very universe lashes out at this breach in space-time. Creatures in the rain must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes {@damage 1d10} damage of each magical damage type (i.e., every damage type except Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing) for a total of {@damage 10d10} damage, or half as much on a success.<br>"
							]
						}
					]
				}
			],
