			"entries": [
				"You distort time at a point you can see within range, creating a shimmering screen of temporal distortion. The screen can be up to 90 feet long, 30 feet high, and 1 inch thick, or a 20-foot Radius dome.",
				"The wall consists of three layers, each distorting time in a different way. When a creature attempts to reach into or pass through the wall, it does so one layer at a time through all the wall's layers. A creature passes through the wall after being subjected to each effect. Creatures of your choice can pass through the wall without being affected.",
				"If you position the wall in a space occupied by a creature, the spell ends instantly without effect.",
				{
					"type": "table",
					"caption": "Layers of the Wall of Time",
					"colLabels": [
						"Distortion",
						"Effect"
					],
					"colStyles": [
						"col-2 text-center",
						"col-10"
					],
					"rows": [
						[
							"Stopped",
							"The creature must succeed a Charisma {@variantrule Saving Throw|XPHB} or become {@condition Paralyzed|XPHB} as they are suspended in animation and do not pass through this layer. The creature can repeat the Save at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on a success and immediately going through the next layer. When a Ranged {@variantrule Weapon Attack|XPHB} passes through the wall, it becomes suspended and does not pass through. When a spell passes through this layer, or the area of a spell overlaps with this layer, the caster must succeed a Charisma {@variantrule Saving Throw|XPHB} or have the spell become suspended and not pass through. The caster can use their action to repeat the Save and force the spell through on a success. All spells and attacks suspended in the wall immediately take effect when the wall disappears}"
						],
						[
							"Slowed",
							"The creature is put under the effects of {@spell Slow}. In this case, the effect persists as long as the wall remains, or until the creature succeeds on a Wisdom Saving Throw at the end of each of its turns."
						],
						[
							"Accelrated",
							"The creature must make a Constitution Saving Throw. On a failure, the creature takes {@damage 20d10} Necrotic damage and ages the equivalent of 5 years for its species for every 20 Necrotic damage it took. {@spell Greater Restoration} can reverse this effect. On a success, a creature takes half damage and suffers no additional effects. When a spell passes through this layer, the caster must succeed a Constitution {@variantrule Saving Throw|XPHB} or the spell fails. Non-magical objects that are not being worn or carried immediately turn to dust when apssing through this layer."
						]
					]
				}
			],
