				"darkvision 120 ft."
			],
			"senseTags": [
				"SD"
			],
			"skill": {
				"perception": "+3",
				"stealth": "+4"
			},
			"trait": [
				{
					"name": "Keen Hearing and Smell",
					"entries": [
						"The chupacabra has {@variantrule Advantage|XPHB} on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on hearing or smell."
					]
				}
			],
			"traitTags": [
				"Keen Senses"
			],
			"action": [
				{
					"name": "Multiattack",
					"entries": [
						"The chupacabra makes two attacks: one with its Claws and one with its Bite."
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Claw",
					"entries": [
						"{@hit 4} to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. {@h}5 ({@damage 1d6 + 2}) Slashing damage. If the target is a creature, it is {@condition grappled} (escape {@dc 13}). Until this grapple ends, the target is {@condition restrained}, and the chupacabra can’t use its claws on another target."
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Bite",
					"entries": [
						"{@hit 4} to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. {@h}5 ({@damage 1d6 + 2}) Piercing damage. If the creature is {@condition grappled} by a successful claw attack, every subsequent round the chupacabra will use its action to attempt to bite the {@condition Grappled|XPHB} creature until said attack succeeds.",
						"Once it succeeds, the chupacabra will {@action Grapple} the victim with its jaws. It does not need to make subsequent attack rolls against this target with its bite, and cannot use its bite attack against another creature. The bite only causes the aforementioned damage on its initial hit. The chupacabra will then start exsanguinating the creature. Each round the creature is held in the bite, it will suffer 1 level of {@condition Exhaustion|XPHB}, starting with the round after the bite initially hits."
					]
				}
			],
			"actionTags": [
				"Multiattack"
			],
			"conditionInflict": [
				"grappled",
				"restrained"
			],
			"environment": [
				"any"
			],
			"fluff": {
				"entries": [
					"In the dead of night, a goat screams in anguish. The farmer rushes from his home, only to find the drained corpses of livestock in the holding pen. The dreaded chupacabra has struck again.",
					"The scourge of ranchers, the chupacabra swoops in on livestock on silent wings, exsanguinating animals. Chupacabras are not above taking domestic animals or even small, unattended children. Once one has settled into an area, locals will do everything they can to eliminate the chupacabra, often hiring advneturers to hunt down and destroy the creature.",
					"The origins of the chupacabra are unknown, but one thing is clear: it is not native to Aureban. Some believe it comes from the Lower Planes, others believe it was the result of a magic experiment gone wrong.",
					"In the wild, they are viewed as something akin to a plague – a blight to be exterminated. People fear their cries, but a scant few have successfully tamed one. These outliers have made excellent guardians and protectors, but their volatile nature makes them prone to turning on their handlers. Despite this, some groups maintain domestication programs.",
					"A chupacabra is, quite frankly, really ugly. It resembles the crossing of a hairless dog with a large monkey. The skin is a dark, mottled gray with sparse, coarse black hairs, mostly along its spinal ridge. It bears large, sharp incisors and stares at the world through blank, dull yellow eyes that shine at night like a cat’s. A large pair of bat-like wings lie folded against its back. Chupacabras make a noise that is half howl, half shriek.",
					"While they are capable of flight, it is ungraceful and they prefer to use their wings to glide down on their prey, exsanguinating it. They usualy hunt alone, but they are sometimes scene hunting in a small family unit; a mating pair and one or two offspring. Their young reach maturity in roughly one year, at which point they split off to start their own family."
				]
			},
			"damageTags": [
				"P",
				"S"
			]
		},
