			"trait": [
				{
					"name": "Keen Smell",
					"entries": [
						"The gumberoo has Advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on smell."
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Rubbery Hide",
					"entries": [
						"Any time the gumberoo is targeted by a ranged attack that deals Bludgeoning, Piercing, or Slashing damage or a melee attack that deals Bludgeoning damage, roll a {@dice d6}. On a 1 to 5, the gumberoo is unaffected. On a 6, the gumberoo is unaffected, and the attack is reflected back at the attacking creature, making it the new target of the attack. If an attack deals multiple types of damage, only the above-defined types are reflected"
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Flammable",
					"entries": [
						"If the gumberoo takes Fire damage, it ignites. While ignited, the gumberoo’s melee attacks deal an additional 4 ({@damage 1d8}) Fire damage, and any flammable object it touches that isn’t being worn or carried ignites. The gumberoo also takes 9 ({@damage 2d8}) Fire damage at the start of each of its turns while it is ignited. Any creature that starts their turn within 15 feet of the ignited gumberoo must succeed on a {@dc 14} Constitution saving throw or become {@condition poisoned} until the start of their next turn due to the noxious fumes from gumberoo’s {@condition burning|MonstersOfDrakkenheim} hide. The only way to extinguish the gumberoo is to douse it in a sufficient amount of water."
					]
				}
			],
			"traitTags": [
