			],
			"environment": [
				"forest"
			],
			"fluff": {
				"entries": [
					"Living among the forest glades of sweetgum trees is a creature too bizarre to be believed. The presense of even a single gumberoo can decimate an entire ecosystem if not disposed of swiftly and carefully.",
					"The gumberoo seems to be some form of bear, though how it came to be is unknown. Its body is round and hairless, covered in a dark, thick hide. The gumberoo’s diet consists heavily of resinous vegitation, such as gum and rubber trees. The elastic material in these plants is incorporated into the monster’s skin, making it stretchy, springy, and incredibly tough.",
					"The ravenous diet of these beasts has made them a target for extermination, but they prove rather difficult to kill. Bullets and arrows have no effect on these monsters, richocheting off its hide and hitting the very hunters that sought to slay it. As such, only blade have any chance to pierce its armored flesh, but even these pose little threat to the gumberoo without magic.",
					"The gumberoo has a single weakness: fire; although it may be wise to avoid it altogether. The monster’s rubbery skin is extremely flammable, setting alite at even the smallest spark. The gumberoo will continue to burn like this until doused in water, causing it extreme pain and sending it into a rage.",
					"Until the gumberoo is killed or stopped, it will thrash wildly about, attacking any creautre and spreading fire to everything it can touch. Such raging animals have torched entire villages and forests when left unattended. Because of this, a spellcaster should think twice before casting a Firebolt at this walking tinderbox."
				]
			},
			"damageTags": [
				"F",
				"P",
				"S"
			],
