				{
					"name": "Luring Lightshow",
					"entries": [
						"The manglerfish moves its lures in a hypnotizing pattern, which lasts until the manglerfish’s {@status Concentration|XPHB} ends on it. {@actSave wis} {@dc 11}, each creature in a 60-foot Emanation originating from the manglerfish that can also see the manglerfish when it takes this action. {@actSaveFail} The target has the {@condition Charmed|XPHB} condition until the effect ends and repeats the save at the end of each of its turns. While {@condition Charmed|XPHB}, the target has the {@condition Incapacitated|XPHB} condition and ignores the Luring Lightshow of other manglerfish. If the target is more than 5 feet from the manglerfish, the target moves on its turn toward the manglerfish by the most direct route, trying to get within 5 feet of the manglerfish. It doesn’t avoid {@action Opportunity Attack}s; however, before moving into damaging terrain (such as lava or a pit) and whenever it takes damage from a source other than the manglerfish, the target repeats the save. {@actSaveSuccess} The target is immune to this manglerfish’s Luring Lightshow for 24 hours."
					]
				}
