			"fluff": {
				"entries": [
					"The manglerfish takes the already unsettling anglerfish and ramps up its features to a truly horrifying degree. Several times larger, a maw twice as wide, and with four bioluminescent lures, the manglerfish fits the definition of a real “sea monster.”",
					"They prefer to prowl deep underwater, preserving energy by allowing ocean currents to move them along and waiting for prey to be lured in by its lights before striking."
				]
			},
