				"charmed",
				"incapacitated",
				"poisoned"
			],
			"fluff": {
				"entries": [
					"The sea harpy is the bane of all sailors who brave uncharted waters. Believed to be nothing more then boogeymen by all but the saltiest of veterens, sea harpies make their nests in underwater caves and on jagged seaside cliffs where crashing waves, submerged rocks, coral reefs, storms, and other natural hazards provide easy prey. Sea harpies attack when crews are already vulnerable, usually once their madening song turns the crew mutinous and draws men into watery graves. Sea harpies use fog, rain, and darkness to ambush from the air or slither up from the depths."
				]
			},
